Title: Brane Surgery

Authors: P.K. Townsend

Comments: Minor corrections. Now in Latex. Needs espcrc2.sty macro. 13 pp. To

appear in Proceedings of the European Research Conference on `AdvancedQuantum Field Theory' held in memory of Claude Itzykson, La lonnde lesMaures, France, Sept. 1996Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys.Proc.Suppl. 58 (1997) 163-175

Some aspects of the role of p-branes in non-perturbative superstring theoryand M-theory are reviewed. It is then shown how the Chern-Simons terms in D=10and D=11 supergravity theories determine which branes can end on which, i.e.the `brane boundary rules'.